*'''[[DVD|DVD]]'''：90年代初有两种高容量光盘标准正在研究阶段；一个是Multimedia Compact Disc，简称MMCD，支持者是日本的索尼和荷兰的飞利浦公司。另一个是Super Density，简称SD，支持者分别是日本的[[东芝|东芝]]、[[松下|松下]]、[[日立製作所|日立]]、[[三菱|三菱]]、[[先鋒_(公司)|先锋]]、[[JVC|JVC]]，美国的[[时代华纳|时代华纳]]和法国的[[汤姆逊|汤姆逊]]公司。为了以免70、80年代[[VHS|VHS]]和[[Beta|Beta]]的标准之战又再出现，MMCD和SD于是将标准合并成为DVD，并于1995年推出。<ref name="DVD">{{Cite web |url=http://didyouknow.org/dvdhistory/ |title=History of DVD |access-date=2013-07-15 |archive-date=2013-07-17 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20130717063412/http://didyouknow.org/dvdhistory/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

*'''[[DVD播放机|DVD播放机]]'''：世界上第一批DVD播放机于1996年11月在日本正式面世，后分别在1997年3月的美国，1998年的欧洲和1999年的澳洲正式面世。<ref name="DVD"/>第一台DVD播放机为1996年9月26日东芝发布的SD-3000，并于11月1日销售，售价77,000日元，随后不同公司也同时推出DVD播放机；<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://museum.toshiba.co.jp/toshiba_history/firsts_products/1998dvd.html |title=Toshiba Science Museum |access-date=2013-07-15 |archive-date=2013-01-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130102155436/http://museum.toshiba.co.jp/toshiba_history/firsts_products/1998dvd.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.brighthub.com/electronics/home-theater/articles/34446.aspx |title=DVD Basics - When Was the First DVD Player Created? |access-date=2013-07-15 |archive-date=2017-06-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170602233126/http://www.brighthub.com/electronics/home-theater/articles/34446.aspx |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.avhelpzone.com/discs/introduction.htm |title=Optical Disc Introduction |access-date=2013-07-23 |archive-date=2017-05-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170514025448/http://www.avhelpzone.com/discs/introduction.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.toshiba.co.jp/about/press/1996_09/pr2603.htm |title=Toshiba Introduces its First DVD-Video Player in Japan |access-date=2013-07-23 |archive-date=2020-10-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201025221124/https://www.toshiba.co.jp/about/press/1996_09/pr2603.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>松下于同日推出DVD-A300和DVD-A100，并推出TH-28GD1内置DVD播放机电视，先锋于22日推出DVL-9和DVL-7；三洋和日立计划在12月推出DVD播放机。<ref>[http://www.telecompaper.com/news/companies-prepare-to-launch-dvd-hardware--93463 COMPANIES PREPARE TO LAUNCH DVD HARDWARE Wednesday 30 October 1996]</ref>

*'''WebTV机顶盒'''：1996年互联网电视在美国首次出现，美国天顶电子公司和Diba公司于1996年5月24日发布全球第一批[[互联网电视|互联网电视]]，称之为NetVision TV，首批两款电视机为售价999美元的27英寸电视和售价3,499美元的35英寸Inteq品牌电视，该电视有内置[[调制解调器|调制解调器]]，可通过遥控浏览网页。同年索尼和飞利浦公司还发布了[[MSN_TV|WebTV]][[数字视频转换盒|机顶盒]]，与电视机分开用，<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://theinventors.org/library/inventors/bl_web_tv.htm |title=The History of WebTV |access-date=2017-09-27 |archive-date=2020-02-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200217042705/http://theinventors.org/library/inventors/bl_web_tv.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.cnet.com/uk/news/zenith-diba-announce-pc-tv-features/ |title=Zenith, Diba announce PC-TV features |access-date=2017-09-27 |archive-date=2017-09-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170927202110/https://www.cnet.com/uk/news/zenith-diba-announce-pc-tv-features/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.nytimes.com/1996/05/10/business/zenith-to-market-a-tv-with-a-modem-and-ethernet-link.html?mcubz=3 |title=Zenith to Market a TV with a Modem and Ethernet Link |access-date=2017-09-27 |archive-date=2017-09-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170927160053/http://www.nytimes.com/1996/05/10/business/zenith-to-market-a-tv-with-a-modem-and-ethernet-link.html?mcubz=3 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://washingtontechnology.com/Articles/1996/07/25/PCTVs-Evolutionary-Wars.aspx |title=PC-TV's Evolutionary Wars |access-date=2017-09-27 |archive-date=2017-09-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170927161120/https://washingtontechnology.com/Articles/1996/07/25/PCTVs-Evolutionary-Wars.aspx |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.forbes.com/1997/09/16/col_side1.html |title=Eeny Meeny Miney Mo:  Catch A Market By Its Toe |access-date=2017-09-27 |archive-date=2017-09-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170927161921/https://www.forbes.com/1997/09/16/col_side1.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>索尼的INT-W100售价349美元，飞利浦的MAT960售价329美元，不包括无线键盘，可浏览网页，服务月费为19.95美元。<ref name="Wildstrom">{{Citation | last = Wildstrom | first = Stephen H. | title = A Web-surfing Box for Peanuts | journal = BusinessWeek | date = 1996-09-16 | url = http://www.businessweek.com/1996/38/b349363.htm | accessdate = 2017-09-27 | archive-date = 2016-04-18 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160418105914/http://www.businessweek.com/1996/38/b349363.htm | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name = "Livingston">{{Citation | last = Livingston | first = Jessica | title = Founders at Work: Stories of Startups Early Days | pages = 173–90 | publisher = Academic Press | year = 2007}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.cedmagic.com/history/webtv-mat960-int-w100.html |title=WebTV - Using a TV to Access the Internet is Launched in 1996 |access-date=2017-09-27 |archive-date=2020-06-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200621173402/http://www.cedmagic.com/history/webtv-mat960-int-w100.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>1997年4月，微软收购WebTV服务，更名MSN TV。

*'''自主人形机器人'''：[[本田|本田]]公司于1986年开始研发行走机器人，前后制出E系列和P系列。1996年12月发布Prototype 2，简称P2，这是世界上第一个自主人形机器人，具备自动调节功能。P2身高1.82米，体重210公斤，共34个自由度关节。由于把主机、32个控制马达、电池、无线通讯等必要的机器全部藏起来，不仅实现了无线遥控，还使它在外观上更像人。机器人可以在普通的路面行走，例如塑料地面、铺设路面、抛光地面等等，也能通过850毫米的狭窄通道；可以上200毫米的台阶，可以跨越150毫米高，150毫米长的障碍物；可以以5公斤的力抓持物体。不过由于机器人太重，行走时能耗为3000瓦，机器人只能工作15分钟。为了解决P2存在的这些问题，于是本田公司开发了新型机器人P3。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://lars.mec.ua.pt/public/LAR%20Projects/Humanoid/2007_PedroFerreira/Anexos/papers%20e%20apresenta%C3%A7%C3%B5es/asimo/P3_spect.pdf |title=The Development of Honda Humanoid Robot Specs |access-date=2013-07-20 |archive-date=2016-03-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304093258/http://lars.mec.ua.pt/public/LAR%20Projects/Humanoid/2007_PedroFerreira/Anexos/papers%20e%20apresenta%C3%A7%C3%B5es/asimo/P3_spect.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Masato">{{Cite web |url=http://rsta.royalsocietypublishing.org/content/365/1850/11.long |title=Honda humanoid robots development |access-date=2013-07-19 |archive-date=2017-10-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171007170505/http://rsta.royalsocietypublishing.org/content/365/1850/11.long |dead-url=no }}</ref>

*'''[[绘文字|绘文字]]'''：早在1967年5月刊登的《[[读者文摘|读者文摘]]》美国月刊就出现过[[表情符号|表情符号]]，<ref>[http://www.snopes.com/computer/internet/smiley.asp Urban Legends Reference Pages: Emoticon (Smiley) Origin<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>但互联网上的表情符号最早于1982年9月19日为{{link-en|史考特·法爾曼|Scott Fahlman}}率先在美国[[卡內基美隆大學|卡內基美隆大學]]的電腦科學[[電子佈告欄|電子佈告欄]] (BBS)上使用。<ref>[http://www-2.cs.cmu.edu/~sef/Orig-Smiley.htm Fahlman's original message] {{Wayback|url=http://www-2.cs.cmu.edu/~sef/Orig-Smiley.htm |date=20080513084941 }} Retrieved February 19, 2009.</ref>最早的非符号表情或图形表情为[[法国|法国]]Smiley Company公司CEO[[尼古拉斯·罗法兰尼|尼古拉斯·罗法兰尼]]发明，1997年至2000年在[[美国版权局|美国版权局]]注册，在1998年也曾以gif格式在互联网上出现。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.licensing.biz/big-interviews/read/smileyworld-s-ceo-nicolas-loufrani-on-plagiarism-the-school-market-and-a-push-for-more-toys/043525 |title=SmileyWorld's CEO Nicolas Loufrani on plagiarism, the school market and a push for more toys |access-date=2017-09-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170805222028/http://www.licensing.biz/big-interviews/read/smileyworld-s-ceo-nicolas-loufrani-on-plagiarism-the-school-market-and-a-push-for-more-toys/043525 |archive-date=2017-08-05 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.smiley.com/emoticons |title=EMOTICONS & EMOJI HISTORY |access-date=2017-09-04 |archive-date=2020-04-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200404160521/https://www.smiley.com/emoticons |dead-url=no }}</ref>使用于移动互联网上的手机非符号表情或表情包为NTT DOCOMO员工栗田穣崇于1999年所设计出，最初他设计的像素的图标表情或绘文字为177个，这是目前常见的移动互联网上流行的表情包或非符号表情，栗田穣崇在1997年4月转入了i-mode的事业部，参与了i-mode的发展计划，栗田穣崇的表情包于同年被搭载在NTT DOCOMO生产的i-mode系统里，提供用户在手机上使用。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2017-02-11/meet-the-man-who-invented-emoji/8249456 |title=Emoji inventor Shigetaka Kurita says MoMA New York acquisition 'feels like a dream' |access-date=2017-09-04 |archive-date=2018-09-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180911042444/http://www.abc.net.au/news/2017-02-11/meet-the-man-who-invented-emoji/8249456 |dead-url=no }}<