78-0471741466, pg.26.</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nttdocomo.co.jp/english/corporate/ir/binary/pdf/library/annual/fy2010/p08_e.pdf |title=Docomo's Service Strategies in the Smartphone Era |access-date=2015-05-19 |archive-date=2016-03-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304122032/https://www.nttdocomo.co.jp/english/corporate/ir/binary/pdf/library/annual/fy2010/p08_e.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>随后日本兴起了移动互联网浪潮和手机文化，2006年日本网络用户为8.53千万，其中81%网络用户通过[[功能手机|功能手机]]上网，<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.infoworld.com/article/2658269/networking/more-mobile-internet-users-than-wired-in-japan.html |title=More mobile Internet users than wired in Japan |access-date=2015-05-18 |archive-date=2017-10-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171016070607/https://www.infoworld.com/article/2658269/networking/more-mobile-internet-users-than-wired-in-japan.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>而全球通过智能手机上网的用户在2015年才达到83%。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://dazeinfo.com/2014/01/23/smartphone-users-growth-mobile-internet-2014-2017/ |title=2 Billion Smartphone Users By 2015 : 83% of Internet Usage From Mobiles |access-date=2015-05-18 |archive-date=2020-11-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111203710/https://dazeinfo.com/2014/01/23/smartphone-users-growth-mobile-internet-2014-2017/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>韩国[[LG_U+|LGT]]于1999年5月提供无线互联网服务。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.prnewswire.co.uk/news-releases/lg-telecom-and-genie-form-strategic-alliance-for-mobile-internet-services-156345945.html |title=LG TeleCom and Genie form strategic alliance for mobile internet services |access-date=2015-05-19 |archive-date=2017-10-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171016015155/http://www.prnewswire.co.uk/news-releases/lg-telecom-and-genie-form-strategic-alliance-for-mobile-internet-services-156345945.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>Mitsuhiro Kagami (2004), Information Technology Policy and the Digital Divide: Lessons for Developing Countries, ISBN 978-1843764137, pg.117.</ref>移动互联网服务并非新概念，美国[[AT&T|AT&T]]和[[Openwave|Unwired Planet]]公司曾于1997年2月10日尝试推出了PocketNet服务，该服务基于[[CDPD|CDPD]]技术，但由于消费用户少，主要用于企业和一些政府部门，最初两款手机分别为[[三菱|三菱]]Mobile Access 120和三星Duette；尽管移动互联网服务在美国出现的比日本早，与日本不同的是美国在1990年代和2000年代初始终都没有形成一个以移动互联网为先或手机文化直到苹果和谷歌公司推出的移动系统才改变了这一切。<ref>[https://sw.csiac.org/techs/abstract/070350 AT&T POCKETNET OFFICIALLY LAUNCHES]{{dead link|date=2018年3月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>Haas, Michael (2006), Management of Innovation in Network Industries: The Mobile Internet in Japan and Europe, ISBN 978-3835003477, pg.63-4.</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.thefreelibrary.com/AT%26T+Wireless+Services+announces+AT%26T+PocketNet+Service+for+business-a019100927 |title=AT&T Wireless Services announces AT&T PocketNet Service for business Feb. 10, 1997 |access-date=2017-10-16 |archive-date=2017-10-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171016175143/https://www.thefreelibrary.com/AT%26T+Wireless+Services+announces+AT%26T+PocketNet+Service+for+business-a019100927 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.nytimes.com/1996/07/12/business/at-t-plans-to-offer-internet-over-a-500-wireless-phone.html |title=AT&T Plans to Offer Internet Over a  Wireless Phone - The New York Times JULY 12, 1996 |access-date=2017-10-16 |archive-date=2017-10-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171016225853/http://www.nytimes.com/1996/07/12/business/at-t-plans-to-offer-internet-over-a-500-wireless-phone.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

